    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The DuPont Pompton Lakes Works, an explosives plant that operated from 1902 to 1994, left a legacy of soil and groundwater contamination.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        6
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://grokipedia.com/page/Pompton_Lakes,_New_Jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "European settlers first arrived in the late 1600s after buying land from the Lenape, marking the area’s earliest permanent habitation.",
